    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically sound example of the definitive analog M-car. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS system that provides a visceral power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and a limited-slip differential, offering tactile engagement and superb corner-exit traction. The suspension geometry remains precise, and the chassis has been proactively addressed with subframe reinforcement to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. Recent service includes a valve clearance adjustment and cooling system overhaul, ensuring the high-strung powertrain operates within optimal thermal and mechanical tolerances. This is a driver-focused machine with excellent compression and a crisp, responsive throttle map.",
      "price": 36500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 48
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used sedan. Good condition. Well-maintained interior. Clean title. Runs smooth.",
